, a small jet also forms at the\ncrest and impacts the front face of the cube just before the circular arc\nreaches zero size. When the bottom of the cube is located at the undisturbed\nwater level the wave impact is dramatically different. In this case, it appears\nthat a packet of air is entrapped during the impact and the surface pressure\nsubsequently oscillates with a frequency of about 2,000 Hz.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 17 Dec 2017 02:38:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-09"}
